name: cust_cmpts
title: Customer Complaints
description:
Each week we send thousands of consumers' complaints about financial products and services to companies for response. Complaints are listed in the database after the company responds or after theyve had the complaint for 15 calendar days, whichever comes first. We publish the consumers description of what happened if the consumer opts to share it and after taking steps to remove personal information. See ourScrubbing StandardandThird Party Studyfor more details.

We dont verify all the facts alleged in these complaints, but we take steps to confirm a commercial relationship. We may remove complaints if they dont meet all of the publication criteria as defined in ourpolicy statement. Data is refreshed nightly.

The Consumer Complaint Database contains complaints we've received about consumer financial products and services, including:

  • Bank accounts or services
  • Consumer loans
  • Credit cards
  • Credit reporting
  • Debt collection
  • Money transfers
  • Mortgages
  • Private student loans
  • Payday loans
  • Prepaid cards
  • Other consumer loan (such as pawn and title loans)
  • Other financial service (such as credit repair and debt settlement)

name: earn
title: Earnings After Graduation
description:
One of the most common reasons students cite in choosing to go to college is the expansion of employment opportunities. To that end, data on the earnings and employment prospects of former students can provide key information. To measure the labor market outcomes of individuals attending institutions of higher education, data on cohorts of federally aided students were linked with earnings data from de-identified tax records and reported back at the aggregate, institutional level.

  • Average and Median Earnings, Disaggregated by Student Subgroups
  • Share of Former Students Earning Over $25,000

name: repay
title: Repayment
description:
To provide a sense for the debt burden of attending college and the loan performance metrics for each school, we produced several elements using the National Student Loan Data System. These elements can provide useful information for students and families concerned about borrowing for college and interested in seeing borrowers behavior after they leave the school.

  • Cohort Default Rate
  • Repayment Rate on Federal Student Loans, Disaggregated by Student Subgroups

It does not provide additional information on cost to the students.

name: nppes_provider
title: NPPES Medical Providers (Doctors)
description:
This table contains (almost) every doctor, nurse, dentist, and medical professional in the US. Each row represents either an organization or an individual practitioner. Some of the columns are exclusive to one type or the other and will be NULL for the rows of the opposite type. For organizations, information will be provided for the whole organization and for the authorizing official. We don't have 2017 data yet, so this is still valid.


Please speak to Michelle Lamfor access.

name: npi_agg_pay
title: NPI Aggregate Provider Payments 2013
description:
This table contains information on the payments made to individual providers (including doctors, dentists, nurses and more).

The primary data source for these data is CMSs CY2013 National ClaimsHistory (NCH) Standard Analytic Files (SAFs) which include claims with dates of service in calendar year 2013 and accreted to the NCH as of 6/30/2014. The NCH SAFs contain 100 percent of Medicare final action claims for beneficiaries who are enrolled in the FFS program.

Data Source: The primary data source for these data is CMSs CY2013 National Claims History (NCH) Standard Analytic Files (SAFs) which include claims with dates of service in calendar year 2013 and accreted to the NCH as of 6/30/2014. The NCH SAFs contain 100 percent of Medicare final action claims for beneficiaries who are enrolled in the FFS program.

Aggregate Payment Information as a by-product of hospital discharges and bills

name: dev_tri
title: Development Triangle
description:
Insurances use a loss development triangle when evaluating loss development. The triangle compares loss development for a specific policy period over an extended period of time. For example, an insurer may look at loss development for the 2010 policy period at twelve-month intervals over the course of five years. This means that it will examine the 2010 loss development in 2010, 2011, 2012, 2013, and 2014.

The datasets aggregated into this table include information on professional indemnity claims, claim forecasts and current claims. This is particularly useful in risk modeling and loss forecasting.

name: repay
title: Repayment
description:
To provide a sense for the debt burden of attending college and the loan performance metrics for each school, we produced several elements using the National Student Loan Data System. These elements can provide useful information for students and families concerned about borrowing for college and interested in seeing borrowers behavior after they leave the school.

  • Cohort Default Rate
  • Repayment Rate on Federal Student Loans, Disaggregated by Student Subgroups

It does not provide additional information on cost to the students.

name: status
title: Flight Status
description:
Flight Status

The flight status is concerned with things like on-time departure and arrival, and whether a flight was cancelled (did not take off) or diverted (landed at the wrong airport). Because of the way flightaware works, we have more data available (about 10 days), but not every flight in the schedule is covered in the status table. An explanation for possible reasons is here [TO-DO].

There may also subtleties like the following:

Each flight is marketed by one (primary) or more airlines (code share partners) and operated by the same primary or another airline. For example, flights from London City to Dsseldorf are marketed by British Airways (BAW), and operated by British Airways Cityflier (CFE) or by Eastern Airways (EZE).

The status table is very rich, and may be used to extract much of the same information contained in the schedule (for example, scheduled departure and arrival times), but it does not have seat capacity information.

There are about 25,000 flights per day in the dataset.

name: deals_by_slr_id_w_m_init
title: Deals by Seller w/ Middle Initial
description:
To help track how much sellers are selling over time, this view is designed to give users the precision of unique-IDs and the readability of names (like sales.deals_by_slr_name). It is generated by joining transactions to a Seller Lookup and showing each sellers' most recent first name, middle initial, and last name (so if the same unique individual closes a few deals while called Xand then changes his/her name to Y, all deals will show up as being closed by Y;and if two people are each named Z, they'll have separate records because they have separate IDs).

First, we calculate each seller's most recent name by finding the latest name change: CREATE Up-to-date Seller Lookup VIEW

Then, we join the up-to-date seller-name lookup with the order record: CREATE Deals by Seller ID w/ Middle Initial VIEW

name: earn
title: Earnings After Graduation
description:
One of the most common reasons students cite in choosing to go to college is the expansion of employment opportunities. To that end, data on the earnings and employment prospects of former students can provide key information. To measure the labor market outcomes of individuals attending institutions of higher education, data on cohorts of federally aided students were linked with earnings data from de-identified tax records and reported back at the aggregate, institutional level.

  • Average and Median Earnings, Disaggregated by Student Subgroups

name: ipps_top_drg
title: Slice - IPPS Top 100 Diagnosis Related Groups 2016
description:
Slice of the ipps.summ_top_drg (IPPS Top 100 Diagnosis Related Groups 2011 ) table that shows a portion of doctor payment information. The data provided here include hospital-specific charges for the more than 3,000 U.S. hospitals that receive Medicare Inpatient Prospective Payment System (IPPS) payments for the top 100 most frequently billed discharges, paid under Medicare based on a rate per discharge using the Medicare Severity Diagnosis Related Group (MS-DRG) for Fiscal Year (FY) 2011, 2012, and 2013. These DRGs represent more than 7 million discharges or 60 percent of total Medicare IPPS discharges.

Hospitals determine what they will charge for items and services provided to patients and these charges are the amount the hospital bills for an item or service. The Total Payment amount includes the MS-DRG amount, bill total per diem, beneficiary primary payer claim payment amount, beneficiary Part A coinsurance amount, beneficiary deductible amount, beneficiary blood deductible amount and DRG outlier amount.

For these DRGs, average charges, average total payments, and average Medicare payments are calculated at the individual hospital level. Users will be able to make comparisons between the amount charged by individual hospitals within local markets, and nationwide, for services that might be furnished in connection with a particular inpatient stay.

name: all_claims
title: Aggregated Claim Stats
description: An aggregation of quarterly claims data -- including both the financial and the demographic details. This table outlines claim information made by the insured for insurer remittance of payment due to injury and loss incurred and covered under their policy agreement. The data includes medical expenses incurred, and compensation to each insured party as well as entities the Part/Nature/Cause codes as part of their reporting standard. The Part/Nature/Cause codes are used to identify the part of body, nature of injury, and cause of loss when reporting workers compensation injuries.

name: store_attributes
title: Store Attributes
description:
This table contains store attributes such as store type.


Location Type ValuesFunctional DescriptionDescription present in existing Attribute definitions
1CorporateA corporate location. Represents locations that facilitate corporate business operations such as settlement processing with third parties
2General StoreA retail Location. A location that provides a consumer access to Best Buy Product (all types) and services for the purpose of creating a transaction.
3Return CenterA product return center. A location where products, with limited ability to resell, are received and diverted to another location based on the best possible physical and/or financial disposition.
4Service CenterA service center location. A location where Best Buy and or Customer products (LPN) can be diagnosed and repaired.
5Whole Sales/MiscA customer fulfillment location. A location which will process (pick product, pack and ship) to complete a customer order from its own inventory.
6Customer Care Center (Not Used)Customer care center. A location which can initiate adjust or cancel a customer orders as well as facilitate fulfillment by sourcing and decrementing the inventory from another location.

name: stu
title: Students
description:
Several elements, including some that havent been published before, identify demographic and other details about the student body of the school. Some of the elements are available through the Integrated Postsecondary Education Data System, and others were produced using the National Student Loan Data System.

  • Number of Undergraduate Students
  • Undergraduate Student Body by Race/Ethnicity
  • Undergraduate Students by Part-Time status
  • Undergraduate Students by Age (25 or Over)
  • Income Brackets of Federal Financial Aid Recipients
  • Share of First-Generation Students
  • Number of FAFSA Submissions to Colleges

Some data were produced as contextual information for the earnings cohorts in particular; the most recent data for these elements are for the 2005 and 2006 cohorts. These data include undergraduate students by: gender, age at entry, veteran status, and marital status.

title: University Cost
description:
Information about the costs to students of a school can provide important context for students and families as they seek to evaluate the tradeoffs of access, affordability, and outcomes.   • Average Cost of Attendance
  • Tuition and Fees
  • Average Net Price, by Income Level

name: new_schedule
title: New Schedule
description:
The flight schedule gets published by airlines up to 330 days in advance. Here, we have the world-wide published schedule for two days in October 2017. The schedule includes the aircraft type and the configuration (first, business, coach) which allows us to get an estimate on the capacity. Airline professionals call this seat capacity "available seats". To take into account the different cost and revenue potential of short- vs. long-haul, you multiply available seats by the distance and get "ASK" (available seat kilometers) or "ASM" (available seat miles).

There are 1,395 airports with scheduled flights, and they are linked with 15,040 distinct flights: City Pairs[+]. As you can see, the most frequent flight connections exist between Mumbai/New Delhi, Sao Paulo/Rio de Janeiro, and Sydney/Melbourne.

name: summ_top_drg
title: Summary of Top Diagnosis Related Groups
description:
The data provided here include hospital-specific charges for the more than 3,000 U.S. hospitals that receive Medicare Inpatient Prospective Payment System (IPPS) payments for the top 100 most frequently billed discharges, paid under Medicare based on a rate per discharge using the Medicare Severity Diagnosis Related Group (MS-DRG) for Fiscal Year (FY) 2011, 2012, and 2013. These DRGs represent more than 7 million discharges or 60 percent of total Medicare IPPS discharges. This data provides insight into doctor payments through medicare.

Hospitals determine what they will charge for items and services provided to patients and these charges are the amount the hospital bills for an item or service. The Total Payment amount includes the MS-DRG amount, bill total per diem, beneficiary primary payer claim payment amount, beneficiary Part A coinsurance amount, beneficiary deductible amount, beneficiary blood deductible amount and DRG outlier amount.

This is the main dashboard we use to analyze this table:

Hospital Revenue Analysis

name: page_visits
title: Page Visits
description: Each row is one time that a user visits an object page in Alation. Object pages include table pages, query pages, column pages, etc. but do not include the home page or other navigational pages. Note that there are some gaps in time where page visit data was not collected for some object types. Check that at least some visits are recorded for the types and time period you care about to make sure your analysis is accurate.
